# SwanStudios Personal Training - Client Data .gitignore
# Purpose: Protect sensitive client data from accidental commits
# Last Updated: 2025-11-05

# ============================================================================
# PHOTOS & MEDIA (NEVER COMMIT - Contains sensitive client images)
# ============================================================================
# Why: Client progress photos and form videos contain identifiable information
# Alternative: Store in encrypted disk image (see SECURITY-PRIVACY-IMPLEMENTATION.md)
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.png
*.gif
*.heic
*.heif
*.mp4
*.mov
*.avi

# Exception: Allow template/placeholder images (if needed)
!templates/*.jpg
!templates/*.png

# ============================================================================
# CLIENT PERSONAL INFORMATION (NEVER COMMIT)
# ============================================================================
# Why: Contains full names, addresses, phone numbers, medical records

# Individual client consent forms with signatures
*/notes/consent.md
*/notes/consent.pdf
*/notes/medical-clearance.pdf

# Private notes with sensitive medical/personal details
*/notes/private-notes.md
*/notes/mental-health-notes.md

# ============================================================================
# EXPORTED/GENERATED FILES (DON'T COMMIT - Regenerate as needed)
# ============================================================================
# Why: Large files, easily regenerated, clutter repository

# PDF exports
*.pdf
exports/*.pdf

# CSV exports
*.csv
exports/*.csv

# Database exports
*.sql
*.db
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3

# ============================================================================
# SYSTEM FILES (OS-SPECIFIC)
# ============================================================================
# Why: Not part of client data, OS-specific clutter

# macOS
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
._*

# Thumbnails
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db

# Windows
desktop.ini
$RECYCLE.BIN/

# ============================================================================
# BACKUP FILES (DON'T COMMIT - Use proper backup strategy)
# ============================================================================
# Why: Backup files should be in separate backup system, not Git

# Automated backups
*.backup
*.bak
*~
*.swp
*.swo

# Backup folders
backup/
backups/
client-data-backup/

# ============================================================================
# ENCRYPTED FILES (DON'T COMMIT - Security risk)
# ============================================================================
# Why: Encrypted disk images and archives should not be in Git

# Encrypted disk images
*.dmg
*.sparseimage
*.sparsebundle

# Encrypted archives
*.zip
*.7z
*.rar
*.tar.gz
*.tar.bz2

# GPG encrypted files
*.gpg
*.asc

# ============================================================================
# ENVIRONMENT & CONFIG (DON'T COMMIT - Contains secrets)
# ============================================================================
# Why: May contain API keys, passwords, tokens

.env
.env.local
.env.production
.env.development

# Stripe keys
stripe-keys.txt
payment-config.json

# Twilio credentials
twilio-credentials.json

# API keys
api-keys.json
secrets.json

# ============================================================================
# LOG FILES (DON'T COMMIT - Generated runtime data)
# ============================================================================
# Why: Log files are generated at runtime, large, not source-controlled

*.log
logs/
*.log.*

# Security audit logs (sensitive)
SECURITY-AUDIT-LOG.md

# Backup logs (contains file paths)
BACKUP-LOG.md

# ============================================================================
# TEMPORARY FILES (DON'T COMMIT - Transient data)
# ============================================================================
# Why: Temporary working files, caches, etc.

tmp/
temp/
*.tmp
cache/

# ============================================================================
# IDE & EDITOR FILES (DON'T COMMIT - Personal preferences)
# ============================================================================
# Why: IDE-specific files, not relevant to other users

# VS Code
.vscode/settings.json
.vscode/launch.json

# JetBrains IDEs
.idea/

# Vim
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# ============================================================================
# WHAT TO COMMIT (Explicitly INCLUDE these)
# ============================================================================
# ✅ Markdown files (README, questionnaires, templates, progress reports)
# ✅ JSON files (Master Prompt templates, schemas)
# ✅ Guide documents (.md files in guides/)
# ✅ Template files (templates/ folder)
# ✅ Registry and tracking files (CLIENT-REGISTRY.md)

# ============================================================================
# NOTES FOR USERS
# ============================================================================
# If you need to commit a file that's ignored:
# 1. Verify it contains NO sensitive data
# 2. Use: git add -f [filename] (force add)
# 3. Better: Update this .gitignore to create exception

# To check what's being ignored:
# git status --ignored

# To verify no sensitive data before commit:
# git diff --cached

# ============================================================================
# END OF .gitignore
# ============================================================================
